By: Chang Yen-yuan
---
Paintings of modern times are brilliant and aim only at perfection, and the
works of our contemporaries are so confused that they have no significance. The
majority of these modern artists belong to the artisan class. ... (They) mix
their brushes and ink with dust and dirt, and their colours with mud, and in
vain smear the silk. How can this be called painting?
